---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Crew Culture" description="Building strong crew culture and shared experiences">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Crew Culture</h1>
  <div class="prose lg:prose-xl mx-auto">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
      <p>Crew culture is the shared values, behaviors, and experiences that define a ruck club's identity. A strong culture fosters belonging, motivation, and long-term commitment among members.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Core Principles</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Shared Purpose: Aligning around common goals and motivations for rucking.</li>
        <li>Mutual Respect: Valuing each member's contributions and differences.</li>
        <li>Shared Suffering: Embracing challenges together builds unbreakable bonds.</li>
        <li>Celebration: Recognizing achievements, both big and small, as a group.</li>
        <li>Tradition: Creating rituals and routines that become part of the club's identity.</li>
        <li>Storytelling: Sharing experiences and lessons learned to inspire others.</li>
        <li>Inclusivity: Ensuring everyone feels they belong and can contribute.</li>
        <li>Accountability: Holding each other to shared standards and commitments.</li>
        <li>Fun: Maintaining enjoyment and camaraderie as central to the experience.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Practical Checklist</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Start each ruck with a brief circle to share intentions.</li>
        <li>End each ruck with a debrief to discuss highlights and lessons learned.</li>
        <li>Create a club motto or slogan that reflects your values.</li>
        <li>Establish regular social gatherings outside of rucks.</li>
        <li>Develop recognition systems for milestones and achievements.</li>
        <li>Create opportunities for members to share their rucking stories.</li>
        <li>Plan occasional themed rucks or challenges to build variety.</li>
        <li>Involve members in decision-making processes for club activities.</li>
        <li>Document and share club history through photos, journals, or blogs.</li>
        <li>Regularly assess cultural health through member feedback.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Downloadable Checklist</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/checklists/crew-culture.pdf" class="btn btn-primary" download>
          Download Printable Checklist (PDF)
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
